{"id":351446,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alan_Bates","text":"Sir Alan Arthur Bates CBE (17 February 1934 - 27 December 2003) was a British actor. He was born in Allestree, Derbyshire.\nBates starred in many movies, including: \"Zorba the Greek\", \"Georgy Girl\", \"Far from the Madding Crowd\", \"The Fixer\", \"The Go-Between\", \"Women in Love\", \"An Unmarried Woman, Gosford Park\" and \"The Rose\". He also acted on stage and television.\nBates was a closeted bisexual. He was married to actress Victoria Ward (1939-1992) from 1970 until her death. They had twin sons: Tristan (1971-1990) and actor Benedick Bates (born 1971). Bates died of pancreatic cancer in London.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Order_of_the_British_Empire","surface_form":"CBE","offset":22},{"uri":"British_people","surface_form":"British","offset":70},{"uri":"Actor","surface_form":"actor","offset":78},{"uri":"Allestree","surface_form":"Allestree","offset":100},{"uri":"Derbyshire","surface_form":"Derbyshire","offset":111},{"uri":"Movie","surface_form":"movie","offset":145},{"uri":"Zorba_the_Greek_(movie)","surface_form":"Zorba the Greek","offset":165},{"uri":"Georgy_Girl","surface_form":"Georgy Girl","offset":184},{"uri":"Far_From_the_Madding_Crowd_(1967_movie)","surface_form":"Far from the Madding Crowd","offset":199},{"uri":"The_Fixer_(movie)","surface_form":"The Fixer","offset":229},{"uri":"The_Go-Between_(movie)","surface_form":"The Go-Between","offset":242},{"uri":"Women_in_Love_(movie)","surface_form":"Women in Love","offset":260},{"uri":"An_Unmarried_Woman","surface_form":"An Unmarried Woman","offset":277},{"uri":"Gosford_Park","surface_form":"Gosford Park","offset":297},{"uri":"The_Rose_(movie)","surface_form":"The Rose","offset":316},{"uri":"Theatre","surface_form":"stage","offset":344},{"uri":"Television","surface_form":"television","offset":354},{"uri":"Closeted","surface_form":"closeted","offset":378},{"uri":"Bisexual","surface_form":"bisexual","offse